2026-04-16 12:33:37 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['ambient sensor module internal relay contacts'] hypothesis_explanation='The PSU delivers a solid 12 V, and this 12 V is present at the control module input with correct polarity. At the relay, the input side of the switched pair sits at 12 V relative to the module negative, but the output side only reaches about 0.36 V, and the same low voltage is observed on the control module output cables. This indicates that the relay’s contacts are not actually closing (or have very high contact resistance), even when the control circuit attempts to turn the lamp on. The symptom of the lamp flickering off briefly every ~20 seconds is consistent with a marginal or intermittently failing relay contact, but the measurements now show it effectively stuck “open” or severely degraded. Therefore the root cause is a faulty relay in the ambient sensor module, specifically its switched contacts, which must be replaced/repair-soldered to restore full 12 V to the load module input.'
